- VSCode Version: 1.8.0-Insiders
- OS Version: Win10

Steps to Reproduce:

1.  Execute the following source code with debugger crashes.
2.  Executing it from command line works fine.

I am compiling the official chat sample from socket.io ( https://github.com/rauchg/chat-example ) in typescript for nodejs.

When pressing F5 the debugger breaks on startup in the json3 module, inside json3.js at line 167 with "Unexpected token 	\t" as error.

When executing app.js directly from command line with node, it works fine.

Please note, i was successfully debugging and working on my application before without any of such problems.
Hopefully my configuration may be wrong and its not a bug of vscode. You can find the code and my launch.json below.
Thx!

````typescript
var app = require('express')();
var http = require('http').Server(app);
var io = require('socket.io')(http);

app.get('/', function (req:any, res:any) {
    res.sendFile(__dirname + '/index.html');
});


io.on('connection', function(socket:any){
  socket.on('chat message', function(msg:any){
    io.emit('chat message', msg);
  });
});

http.listen(3000, function () {
    console.log('listening on *:3000');
});

